    * United States:
          o _P_u_b_l_i_c_ _e_m_p_l_o_y_e_e_ _p_e_n_s_i_o_n_s
          o _R_e_t_i_r_e_m_e_n_t_ _p_l_a_n_s_ _i_n_ _t_h_e_ _U_n_i_t_e_d_ _S_t_a_t_e_s
          o _S_o_c_i_a_l_ _S_e_c_u_r_i_t_y
********** MMaarrkkeett ssttrruuccttuurree[[_ee_dd_ii_tt_ _ss_oo_uu_rr_cc_eeÂÂ || _ee_dd_ii_tt]] **********
The market for _p_e_n_s_i_o_n_ _f_u_n_d investments is still centered around the U.K.and
U.S. economies.[_c_i_t_a_t_i_o_n_ _n_e_e_d_e_d] Japan and the EU are conspicuous by absence.
[_c_i_t_a_t_i_o_n_ _n_e_e_d_e_d] As of 2005 the U.S. was the largest market for pension fund
investments followed by the UK.[_c_i_t_a_t_i_o_n_ _n_e_e_d_e_d]
Pension reforms have gained pace worldwide in recent years and funded
arrangements are likely to play an increasingly important role in delivering
retirement income security and also affect securities markets in future years.
********** OObbttaaiinniinngg ssuurrvveeyy ddaattaa oonn ppeennssiioonnss[[_ee_dd_ii_tt_ _ss_oo_uu_rr_cc_eeÂÂ || _ee_dd_ii_tt]] **********
Numerous worldwide health, aging and retirement surveys contain questions
pertaining to pensions. The _M_e_t_a_ _D_a_t_a_ _R_e_p_o_s_i_t_o_r_y - created by the non-profit
RAND Corporation and sponsored by the National Institute on Aging at the
National Institutes of Health - provides access to meta data for these
questions as well as links to obtain respondent data from the originating
surveys.
********** SSeeee aallssoo[[_ee_dd_ii_tt_ _ss_oo_uu_rr_cc_eeÂÂ || _ee_dd_ii_tt]] **********
